This place has been here for over 20 plus years. Used to be the only Chinese restaurant I would go to and I have been going here since I was a teenager. I am now in my 40s. However, recently new management took over and it's sad to say but the food is not the same. I would usually get chicken egg foo young, fried rice, pepper steak or Mongolian beef. The Mongolian beef is still good, but the beef is suspect as it is too tender. The dishes have fell off. Previously the fried rice was fresh and you can tell fresh ingredients were in it. Now that doesn't seem to be the case. The fried rice taste like it is leftover from a previous day and they add too much soy sauce when cooking it. The lady taking the orders is not all that friendly and has a slight attitude when you ask her a question. The previous owners were not like this. The prices have gone up. Who pays $2.80 extra to add brocolli to fried rice. That is highway robbery. You can get two eggrolls for that price. In addition, they charge .8 cents per pack for soy sauce or sweet and sour sauce. It used to be 5 cent. I didn't used to come here often since I stay on the other side of town, but now I won't be rushing to come out here at all. Worst thing is I am allergic to shellfish and when I got my chicken fried rice the other day there was a piece of shrimp in it. Luckily, I noticed it before eating, but this should never happen. I called and the lady of course had a slight attitude and didn't believe me. I had to drive back up there to show her. That was the last straw. I have never experienced this before of all the years coming here. I literally could have died because of how severe my allergy is, but thankfully I didn't so I can tell my story to people to not go here.
